{"questionId":"24173706","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>It is given that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mo>≠</mo><mn>1</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>Note:</strong> There are many valid approaches to the question, and the steps may be seen in different ways. Some possible methods are given here, but candidates may use a combination of one or more of these methods.<br><br>In all methods, the final <em><strong>A</strong></em> mark is awarded for working which leads directly to the <em><strong>AG</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to isolate <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math> or a power of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>correct working&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>b</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>taking logarithm to base <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></math> on both sides&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></math></p>\n<p>correct application of log rules leading to equation in terms of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo> </mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo> </mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo> </mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo> </mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mn>3</mn></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Candidates may substitute <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math> at any point in their working.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 3</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math></p>\n<p>writing in terms of base&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>correct application of log rules&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>writing&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp;in terms of base&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>correct working&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mfenced></mstyle></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 4</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A2</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"24173706","referenceCode":"22N.1.SL.TZ0.8b.i","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that logab b=-2.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra",